Name: Davis KWIK-X Quickfit LED Emergency Exit 3W
Description:
KWIK-X has been designed specifically to take the hassle out of installation. Simply attach the mounting cover to a wall, ceiling or suspension system, connect the mains supply, then slide the main body straight on and secure. It’s that easy! And the light weight ABS construction makes this unit ideal for mounting on ceiling tiles or plaster walls.

KWIK-X utilises 50,000 hr LEDs and draws only 3W, allowing for wide-spread application throughout the premises whilst maintaining a modest power consumption. The unit complies with AS/NZS60598.2.22 and is backed by a three-year full warranty on the complete fitting.

Features

  • Quick connect bracket for ceiling, wall or suspension mount
  • Fire-retardant ABS/PC construction
  • Long life 50,000 hr LEDs
  • Rechargeable high temperature NiCad battery
  • Viewing distance 24m
  • Legends: running man with left/right arrows
  • 2 x running man with no arrows

Applications

  • Greenstar rated buildings
  • Shopping centres, showrooms, retail outlets
  • Motels, hotels
  • Lecture theatres, schools, auditoriums, halls
  • Restaurants, cafeterias
  • Transit areas, lounges, waiting rooms

Standards

Manufactured under ISO 9001:2008 to standards:

  • AS/NZS60598.1
  • AS/NZS60598.2.1
  • AS/NZS60598.2.22
  • AS/NZS2293.3
  • AS/NZS CISPR 15

Name: X-IT LED EMERGENCY EXIT luminaire 3W Recessed
Description:
X-IT brings to the market a new quality in LED technology design with the illumination of the pictogram and uniformity of illumination surpassing AS/NZS60598.2.22. This ensures visibility to persons within the escape route, with the directional signage allowing for prompt and safe evacuation.

X-IT has been designed specifically with aesthetics in mind. The unit may be installed in the traditional pendant mount manner or, for something a little more stylish, a facia plate is provided to allow for recessed mounting. Simply slide the plate on and clip it into position, and the fitting is now ready for mounting in plaster or solid ceilings – as easy as installing a down light.

Features

  • Energy efficient electronic control gear
